e screen. The camera automatically turns on when you open an app that can take pictures, record videos, or make video calls.</p><div id=\"mchl0940e7e2\" class=\"Task no-header\"><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchl0940e7e2\"><ul class=\"ListSingle\"><li><p><em>Turn the camera on:</em> On your Mac, open an app that can use the camera, such as FaceTime, Messages, or Photo Booth. A green light beside the camera glows to indicate that the camera is on.</p></li><li><p><em>Turn the camera off:</em> On your Mac, close or quit all apps that can use the camera. The green light beside the camera turns off, showing that the camera is off.</p></li></ul></div></div><p>To learn more about using your camera with the apps mentioned, see <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?product=facetime&amp;locale=en_US&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">FaceTime User Guide</a>, <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?product=messages&amp;locale=en_US&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">Messages User Guide</a>, and <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?product=photo-booth&amp;locale=en_US&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">Photo Booth User Guide</a>.</p><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-peoples-pictures&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL3A930A6A&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Change people’s pictures in apps on Mac</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["DisplayVersion/macOS Mojave 10.14","IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","ContentMode/liveContent","ArchivalStatus/Unarchived","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexON","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON"